### Access Control Hierarchy

Each schema's database roles inherit up to the database level:

```
Database: {{ data_product_name | upper }}_<ZONE>
├── DB_R (Database Read)
│   {%- for config in schema_configuration %}
│   {%- set schemas = config.schemas.split(',') | map('trim') | list %}
│   {%- for schema in schemas %}
│   ├── SC_R_{{ schema | upper }}
│   {%- endfor %}
│   {%- endfor %}
├── DB_W (Database Write)
│   {%- for config in schema_configuration %}
│   {%- set schemas = config.schemas.split(',') | map('trim') | list %}
│   {%- for schema in schemas %}
│   ├── SC_W_{{ schema | upper }}
│   {%- endfor %}
│   {%- endfor %}
└── DB_C (Database Create)
    {%- for config in schema_configuration %}
    {%- set schemas = config.schemas.split(',') | map('trim') | list %}
    {%- for schema in schemas %}
    ├── SC_C_{{ schema | upper }}
    {%- endfor %}
    {%- endfor %}
```

### Schema Properties

All schemas will be created with:
- **Managed Access:** `WITH MANAGED ACCESS` (centralized grant control)
- **Owner:** `{{ data_product_name | upper }}_ADMIN` role
- **Database Role Owner:** `{{ data_product_name | upper }}_RBAC` role
